<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-187-122  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 187 122.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Seybold Report on Publishing Systems  Feb 12 1990 v19 n10p21(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Seybold Publications Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Agfa CG enhances Integrator graphics.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Agfa Corp. AGFA Compugraphic Div. (product enhancement).andO;Product:   Integrator Graphiti (Computer program) (product introduction)PowerPro 3.0 (Computer program) (product enhancement).andO;Topic:     EnhancementsGraphics Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Better link to Macintosh added At Type-X last year, Agfa Compugraphicintroduced a graphic system for its Integrator line that supported the Focusscanner for input and Paint and Draw programs for manipulating graphicelements within the workstation.andP;  The graphic system has now been enhancedwith the release of two software packages: Integrator Graphiti and PowerPro3.0.andM;The former product converts graphics from foreign devices (Mac, PC or Sunworkstations) into Integrator Draw and Paint files, where they can be editedusing the Integrator's own graphics capabilities.andP;  Files are accessed from aDOS floppy disk or via Tops network.andP;  Both LocalTalk and EtherTalkconfigurations will be supported.andM;Formats supported initially are PIC, PICT, WordPerfect, TIFF and Sun Raster.andO;Contone images can be converted to halftones by applying user-selectedhalftone screens.andP;  Graphics can be scaled, fonts substituted and then viewedwithin Graphiti.andM;PowerPro 3.0 supports creation of round-corner boxes with user-defined ruleweights for the four sides and radii.andP;  Boxes can be filled, tints degraded(horizontally or vertically), and so on.andM;PowerPro also supports scanning and screening contone images using the Focusdevice.andO;</TEXT></DOC>